Add request params.

Added concept of a `RequestField`.

A `RequestField` is a data container the encapsulates what data is needed to
build post bodies of various forms. The `encode_multipart_formdata` function
was adjusted to always expect objects of type `RequestField`, and a backwards
compatible factory-style method was added to account for the old tuple-style
way of passing around the post body fields.

For inspiration of the change, see
https://github.com/shazow/urllib3/issues/215

Adding a __contextTriples index allows us to efficiently look-up
all triples in one context at linear cost of the store's size.
This is a common operation for example during serialization.

The previous implementation got along without this index, but
serializing a dataset with a lot of graphs took quadratic time.

Change how the Authorize.net auto-discovery works.

This was precipitated by Authorize.net changing their response in the
sandbox for the wrong transaction ID.  We can no longer call
retrieve('0') to the sandbox API.  It was the favorite call because it
is idempotent and we don't have to worry about changing any data by
calling it, however it had some disadvantages, namely that the
Transaction Details API is not always enabled for every customer.  We
switched to voiding a non-existent transaction because that endpoint
should exist for every customer.

Additionally, the auto-discovery code has been moved out of __init__,
which means that the gateway URL isn't discovered at configure time, but
it also means that your entire application doesn't fail when you
Authorize.net decides to change their response codes.

Co-authored-by: Gavin Wahl <gwahl@fusionbox.com>

Connect signals for real-time search index updates

The codebase had not been updated to use the signal processors pattern
(see
http://django-haystack.readthedocs.org/en/latest/signal_processors.html)
used to implement real-time search index updating in Haystack 2.0+.

This commit moves the connection and disconnection logic out of
the ``StoryIndex`` class and into a custom signal processor classs,
``storybase.search.signals.RealtimeSignalProcessor``. It also wires
up handlers to update the index for ``Help`` models.

The implementation is a little verbose, but I think that's ok in the
interest of clarifying what's being wired up.

Updates:
1) I gave the parent location object its own file just to reduce the
size of the locations.py file.

talk() function, which provides your first meeting with King Vinny.  And
Valley_End, aka the Valley of Forbidden Objects, has a menu including a
dig() function.  The dig() function allows you to dig in random places
and find treasures or get into fights with monsters.
3) I created a mission that stems from your first meeting with King
Vinny: King Vinny sends you to dig up a treasure in the Valley of
Forbidden Objects where you will encounter the first boss.

other functions and objects that have to do with Shmucksburg's armory.
The end goal here is that Shumcksburg will be able to defend itself
using its armory while your hero is away.  You can't see any of this in
action yet.
